    <h2>4. Bangalore: Technology-Forward Equipment and Custom Fabrication</h2>
    <p>Bangalore's bakery equipment manufacturing scene is less about mass production and more about custom, technology-forward solutions. The presence of a large cloud kitchen industry and well-funded F&B startups has pushed Bangalore fabricators to excel at modular designs, IoT-enabled equipment, and compact urban kitchen solutions.</p>

    <h3>Key Bangalore Manufacturers</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Peenya Industrial Fabricators (Peenya Industrial Estate):</strong> Stainless steel custom fabrication for bakeries and cloud kitchens. From prep tables to walk-in cold rooms to custom display cases. Quick turnaround (10–20 days) and strong design collaboration. No MOQ for custom work. Pricing 10–15% above Coimbatore but with far better service and faster delivery.</li>
      <li><strong>Kaizen Kitchen Equipment (Bommasandra):</strong> Manufacturer of commercial refrigeration, display cabinets, and modular kitchen systems. Strong client list includes major hotel chains and QSR brands. Factory-direct pricing available with 50% advance. Lead time 15–20 days standard.</li>
      <li><strong>Sterling Bakery Systems (Peenya):</strong> Focuses on commercial convection ovens and proofers. Targets mid-market cloud kitchens and standalone bakeries. Warranty: 18 months parts, 12 months labour — above industry average. Service centres in Bangalore, Chennai, and Hyderabad.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>When to Buy from Bangalore</h3>
    <p>Bangalore manufacturers make most sense if: (1) you're in South India; (2) you need custom stainless steel fabrication; (3) you value responsive after-sales service; or (4) you're equipping a cloud kitchen with modular, space-efficient equipment. They're generally not the cheapest option, but the design capability and service quality are among the best in India.</p>

    <h2>5. Kolkata: Value-Segment Specialists and Confectionery Equipment</h2>
    <p>Kolkata has a long tradition of bakery and confectionery — the city's Bengali sweetshops (mishti dokan) and the legacy of colonial-era bakeries (Flury's, Nahoum's) created a local demand for commercial baking equipment that predates modern Indian manufacturing. The Howrah and Belgachia industrial areas have clusters of small to mid-size manufacturers making budget-friendly ovens, mixers, and confectionery machines.</p>

    <h3>Key Kolkata Manufacturers</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Eastern Bakery Equipment (Howrah):</strong> Budget-segment manufacturer of convection ovens, deck ovens, and bread proofers. Pricing is among the lowest in India — a 6-tray convection oven ex-factory at ₹32,000–₹42,000. Quality is functional rather than premium. Suitable for high-street bakeries and small-town setups where price is the primary constraint.</li>
      <li><strong>Bengal Food Machinery (Belgachia, Kolkata):</strong> Specialises in confectionery equipment — sandesh moulds, mishti machinery, chocolate tempering units, and packaging for sweets. Unique to this cluster. Exports to Bangladesh and Nepal. Custom confectionery tooling is a strength.</li>
      <li><strong>Calcutta Kitchen Works (Ultadanga):</strong> Full-range manufacturer covering ovens, mixers, refrigeration, and stainless steel fabrication. Good value option for East Indian buyers who want to avoid logistics costs from Delhi or Coimbatore. Service network across West Bengal, Odisha, and Northeast India.</li>
    </ul>

